```json
{
  "application": "USEARCH",
  "other_software": [
    "QIIME",
    "FastTree",
    "RDP Classifier",
    "rsync",
    "gunzip",
    "find",
    "cat",
    "mv",
    "rm",
    "biom",
    "align_seqs.py",
    "filter_otus_from_otu_table.py",
    "filter_fasta.py",
    "assign_taxonomy.py",
    "make_phylogeny.py",
    "single_rarefaction.py",
    "collapse_samples.py",
    "alpha_rarefaction.py",
    "alpha_diversity.py",
    "beta_diversity.py"
  ],
  "resource_requirements": {
    "walltime": "18:00:00",
    "memory": "264Gb",
    "nodes": "1",
    "processors_per_node": "8"
  }
}
```

This script uses **USEARCH** as its primary application for sequence analysis, specifically for OTU picking and sequence clustering. It utilizes several other tools for various tasks, as outlined in the "other_software" section. 

The script requires significant computational resources, including 18 hours of walltime, 264 GB of memory, and 8 processors on a single node, as specified in the "resource_requirements" section.
